commitResults.messageTitle: Implement RFC 5322 email validation with character limit
commitResults.messageBody:
Add email validation following RFC 5322 standard with a 998 character
limit. The implementation uses a regex pattern that validates both the
local-part and domain portions of email addresses according to RFC 5322
specifications.

Features:
- Validates email format according to RFC 5322
- Enforces maximum length of 998 characters
- Supports special characters in local-part: !#$%&'*+-/=?^_`{|}~
- Allows hyphens, underscores, and periods in local-part
- Validates domain structure with proper labels

Limitations:
- Does not support comments in email addresses
- Does not support spaces in quoted strings (e.g., "peter jack"@example.com)
- Does not support IP addresses as domain (e.g., user@[192.168.1.1])
